It was always Solomon Mabotja’s dream to publish a book. After writing for many years without being published, his dream has come true. The 51-year-old – who lives in Vosloorus, Ekurhuleni told Daily Sun he has been writing since he was young. His first book, You Touched Women Again, was published on 30 May. In the book, he talks about psychological and emotional abuse through the story of a married woman. He works as an adult education teacher, and has seen how illiteracy affects people’s lives. He said the book also talks about how many adults tend to sign documents without reading them through. Solomon said his love of reading inspired him to start writing. He writes drama, poetry and short stories. He said publishing his first book was exciting. “This success makes me want to write more books.” He said he has many manuscripts he intends to publish.